{
  "texts": [
    "An adaptive downsample mechanism, referred to as the channel attention module, is incorporated into this transition layer.",
    "Figure 4 illustrates that the channel attention mechanism processes feature channels in two stages: \"squeeze\" and \"excitation.",
    "\"Our proposal involves utilizing the squeeze-and-excitation network following each residual block to facilitate the learning of interdependencies among various feature maps.",
    "During the squeeze stage, the input features undergo compression into a one-dimensional (1-D) vector with a length equivalent to the number of channels.",
    "The initial input feature has a size of H x W x C, where H x W represents the spatial domain size and C is the number of channels."
  ]
}